{
  "texts": [
    "This model was a deviation from our preregistration (which included only two random intercepts, one of participant id and another of vignette id), but was modified because we concluded it was the most appropriate model given the structure of the data where multiple raters were rating the same reappraisal.",
    "We estimated degrees of freedom using the Satterthwaite method and used the Estimated Marginal Means package (Lenth et al., 2024) to calculate the contrasts.",
    "We created four of these models for each outcome of reappraisal quality.",
    "(See Supplemental Information for separate model outputs.)",
    "We first compared the quality of the reappraisals between humans and GPT."
  ]
}